title: Use This Hinge Opener Formula To Get More Dates
caption: false

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

How did you come up with that? Yeah so what I like to do with the hinge, if I can find something unusual about their profile no one else is finding, I like to mention that. It's like double points if you can like pick two things on the profile. And then like the third thing I usually try to go with is if I can create this story or fantasy about us dating already. I love this strategy, my only concern is the return on investment from that. Would you use the same strategy if you're getting way more matches? Yeah the only thing I can compare her to was like summer time I was living in a city in Ireland, Cork. Most replies I would have got would have been from that sort of a message. You know just like pile of dirty clothes on behind her and she's taking a really hot picture where most guys might go oh you look really cute or something. I'll go like so when we end up dating I don't want you leaving clothes laying around my house or something like that. Like I'll pick out something smaller than that. Usually that gets it like a haha it's a story going and then you kind of like start bickering about what you're gonna fight about when you're already dating.
